---
import TextmodeLayout from "../layouts/textmode/TextmodeLayout.astro";

const releasesUrl = "https://github.com/12yanogden/umoria-rust/releases";
---

<TextmodeLayout title="Downloads" description="Build Umoria from source or check GitHub Releases for binaries.">
  <article class="stub-screen downloads-page">
    <h1>Downloads</h1>

    <p>
      Primary platforms are Unix-like systems with ncurses — <strong>macOS</strong> and
      <strong>Linux</strong>. Distributed via git only (crate <code>publish = false</code>; not on
      crates.io). Windows is not a proven target.
    </p>

    <section>
      <h2>Build from source</h2>
      <p>Requirements: a recent stable Rust toolchain, system ncurses, and pkg-config.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>macOS (Homebrew): <code>brew install ncurses pkg-config</code></li>
        <li>Debian/Ubuntu: <code>sudo apt-get install libncurses-dev pkg-config</code></li>
      </ul>
      <pre class="textmode-pre"><code>cargo build --release</code></pre>
      <p>The binary is <code>target/release/umoria</code>.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Release artifacts</h2>
      <p>
        Prebuilt binaries may appear on GitHub Releases when available (the page may be empty for
        now).
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href={releasesUrl}>GitHub Releases</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</TextmodeLayout>
